@startuml Module Architecture (After v2.0 Refactoring)
!theme plain
title Nova Firmware Module Architecture (v2.0)\nAfter Comprehensive Refactoring

package "Application Layer" {
  [task_motor.c\n1,207 lines] as TaskMotor
  [task_ui.c] as TaskUI
  [task_tapping.c] as TaskTapping
  [task_depth.c] as TaskDepth
  [main.c] as Main
}

package "Feature Modules\n(Phase 2 Extraction)" {
  [spindle_hold.c\n150 lines\nPhase 2.1] as SpindleHold
  [jam.c\n282 lines\nPhase 2.3] as Jam
  [temperature.c\n164 lines\nPhase 2.2] as Temperature
  [diagnostics.c\n320 lines\nPhase 7] as Diagnostics
}

package "Control Layer" {
  [motor.c\n1,038 lines] as Motor
}

package "Protocol Layer\n(Phase 6)" {
  [motor_protocol.c\n208 lines\n23 unit tests] as Protocol
}

package "Utility Layer\n(Phase 3)" {
  [utilities.c\n25 lines\n7 unit tests] as Utils
  [shared.h\ndelay_ms()\nMOTOR_CMD] as Shared
}

package "Hardware Layer" {
  [USART3\nMotor MCB\n9600 baud] as UART3
  [USART1\nDebug Console\n9600 baud] as UART1
  [GPIO\nPD4 Motor Enable] as GPIO
}

' Dependencies - Application Layer
TaskMotor --> Motor : motor_*() API
TaskMotor --> SpindleHold : spindle_hold_*()
TaskMotor --> Jam : jam_load_update()
TaskMotor --> Temperature : temp_monitor_update()
TaskMotor --> Protocol : send_query()\nsend_command()
TaskMotor --> Diagnostics : diagnostics_*()

TaskUI --> Main : g_event_queue
TaskTapping --> Main : g_event_queue
TaskDepth --> Main : g_state (depth)

Main --> Motor : MOTOR_CMD macro
Main --> Diagnostics : diagnostics_init()

' Dependencies - Feature Layer
SpindleHold --> Motor : motor_send_command()
SpindleHold --> Shared : delay_ms()

Jam --> Shared : SEND_EVENT()
Temperature --> Motor : motor_read_param()
Temperature --> Shared : SEND_EVENT()

' Dependencies - Control Layer
Motor --> Protocol : protocol_build_*\nprotocol_parse_*()
Motor --> Utils : int_to_decimal_str()
Motor --> Shared : delay_ms()
Motor --> UART3 : Direct register\naccess

' Dependencies - Protocol Layer
Protocol --> Utils : int_to_decimal_str()

' Dependencies - Diagnostics
Diagnostics --> Shared : g_event_queue\ng_motor_cmd_queue

' Hardware access
TaskMotor --> UART3 : USART3 TX/RX
TaskMotor --> GPIO : PD4 enable/disable
Main --> UART1 : Serial console

note right of Protocol
  **Phase 6: Extracted**

  Reusable protocol layer:
  • Packet building
  • Response parsing
  • Frame validation
  • Checksum calculation

  Tested: 16 unit tests ✅
end note

note right of Diagnostics
  **Phase 7: New Module**

  Real-time monitoring:
  • UART timeouts
  • Queue depth/overflows
  • Protocol statistics
  • MCB comm health
  • System uptime

  Commands:
  STATS, ERRORS, PERF
end note

note bottom of SpindleHold
  **Phase 2.1: Extracted**
  115 lines from task_motor.c

  Powered position lock
  discovered via logic analyzer
end note

note bottom of Jam
  **Phase 2.3: Expanded**

  Multi-mode jam detection:
  • State-based (startup, stall)
  • Load-based (sustained, spike)
end note

note bottom of Temperature
  **Phase 2.2: Expanded**

  Dual sensor monitoring:
  • GD32 internal (HMI board)
  • MCB heatsink (via T0 query)

  Threshold with hysteresis
end note

note bottom of Utils
  **Phase 3.3: Created**

  Common helpers:
  • int_to_decimal_str()

  Tested: 7 unit tests ✅
end note

@enduml
